---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

export const title = "Brunswick Dispensary Guide";
---

<Layout 
  title="Brunswick Dispensary Guide | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Complete guide to opening a cannabis dispensary in Brunswick, Maine. Market analysis, regulations, and investment requirements."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500916434205-0c77489c6cf7?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Brunswick Dispensary Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">How to open a cannabis dispensary in Brunswick, Maine</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Brunswick, a historic coastal town in Cumberland County with 21,000+ residents, offers a unique opportunity in the Greater Portland metro area. Home to Bowdoin College and a growing biotech sector, Brunswick combines a educated demographic with lower costs than Portland, making it an attractive option for cannabis entrepreneurs. Before moving forward, familiarize yourself with the <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-real-estate/">real estate requirements</a> essential for success.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Brunswick: A Local Opportunity" type="passion">
      Operating in Brunswick is more than just a business; it's about becoming a pillar of the community. Focus on local engagement and education to build lasting trust with your neighbors.
    </Callout>


    <section>
      <h2>Why Brunswick?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Portland Metro</strong> - Access to larger market</li>
        <li><strong>Bowdoin College</strong> - Educated demographic</li>
        <li><strong>Biotech Growth</strong> - Young professionals</li>
        <li><strong>Coastal Location</strong> - Appeals to quality-of-life</li>
        <li><strong>Moderate Costs</strong> - Lower than Portland</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Brunswick Market</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Factor</th><th>Assessment</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Population</td><td>21,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Metro Area</td><td>Portland Metro</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Competition</td><td>Low</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Real Estate</td><td>Moderate ($16-24/sq ft)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Access</td><td>Route 1, I-295</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local Regulations</h2>
      <p>Under <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine OCP regulations</a>, Brunswick operators must:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Obtain state license from Maine Office of Cannabis Policy</li>
        <li>Confirm local zoning compliance</li>
        <li>Meet all state compliance requirements</li>
        <li>Complete employee authorizations</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Best Locations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Maine Street</strong> - Historic downtown</li>
        <li><strong>Route 1</strong> - High traffic commercial</li>
        <li><strong>Cook's Corner</strong> - Shopping area</li>
        <li><strong>Near Bowdoin</strong> - College-area business</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Investment Requirements</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>Estimated Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Real Estate (lease)</td><td>$2,500-4,000/mo</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Build-out</td><td>$85,000-150,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Total Investment</td><td>$340,000-580,000</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine Cannabis Rules</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Consult with qualified professionals.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
